item.title: Pence cautious after aide tests positive
item.description: Vice President Mike Pence has been self-isolating at home after an aide tested positive for the coronavirus last week, but he plans to return to the White House on Monday.

item.title: Miners still critical after gas explosion
item.description: The lives of four miners continue to hang in the balance after an underground gas explosion at a central Queensland coalmine.

item.title: Jury duty resumes with temperature checks
item.description: NSW residents will be summoned for jury duty this week as the District Court promises to introduce methods to keep jurors safe during the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Japan eyes spending to fight virus slump
item.description: Japan will take additional stimulus measures "swiftly" to combat the fall-out from the coronavirus pandemic, Prime Minister Shinzo Abe says, signalling readiness for a second supplementary budget in the current Diet session running through June.

item.title: Union leader Jack Mundey dies, aged 90
item.description: Trade union leader and environmental activist Jack Mundey has been hailed as a visionary whose legacy will "echo through the ages", after his death at the age of 90.

item.title: French to return to shops and hair salons
item.description: Millions of French people are set to cautiously emerge from one of Europe's strictest lockdowns, once more able to engage in everyday activities that have become unexpectedly precious, such as visiting shops and getting their hair cut.

item.title: Bushfire-hit towns get $650m for recovery
item.description: Bushfire-ravaged towns will receive $650 million as they work to recover from the devastating summer bushfires.

item.title: NZME makes Stuff media powerplay
item.description: New Zealand's biggest media company NZME has stunned media rival Stuff with a $NZ1 takeover offer in a reboot of the "StuffMe" merger.

item.title: New course fills the chronic pain gap
item.description: A new way of treating chronic pain is attracting global attention, and for sufferers like Adelaide woman Freiya Reef Macnicol it's been a godsend.

item.title: Covid rapid response teams to hit Victoria
item.description: Rapid response squads will be established to tackle any new Victorian outbreaks of coronavirus as part of a $20 million package.
